<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-03-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-03-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="76" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Bridgman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-03-04"><hi rend="italic">March 4,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 76.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your unnumbered dispatch
                            written at Keene, N. H., August 16, last, I have to say that you press
                            again, and urgently, for the prompt trial or discharge of Capt. John S.
                            Bowles, who was arrested October 4, 1894.</p>
                        <p>You will report the result of your action to the Department.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>